 84], [32, 96], [32, 108], [32, 120], [33, 0], [33, 12], [33, 24], [33, 36], [33, 48], [33, 60], [33, 72], [33, 84], [33, 96], [33, 108], [33, 120], [33, 132], [34, 0], [34, 12], [34, 24], [34, 36], [34, 48], [34, 60], [34, 72], [34, 84], [34, 96], [35, 0]]}, "lines": {"text": ["City of Arcata Transportation Safety Committee", "Annual Report to the City Council", "Presented at the June 6, 2007 City Council Meeting", "Committee Members", "Stan Elcock, Chair", "Eric Wennerholm, Vice-Chair", "Elias Elias", "Peggy Martinez", "Marguerite Powers (appointed August 2006)", "Christopher Rall (appointed November 2006)", "Oona Smith (through February 2007)", "Staff Liaisons:", "R. Charles (Doby) Class, Public Works Director", "Monica Campbell, Public Works Administrative Assistant", "Captain Tom Chapman or Lieutenant Ryan Peterson, Arcata Police Department", "The Transportation Safety Committee (TSC) was recreated by the City Council by adoption of", "Ordinance No. 1292 effective 6/18/99. The Powers and duties of this committee are to review", "all transportation safety matters and make recommendations to the Council, commissions, or", "City staff as appropriate.", "During the past year the TSC held twelve regular meetings on the third Tuesday of each month.", "This would equate to approximately 237 hours of volunteered time and at least 58 hours of City", "staff time.", "One of the major attributes of the TSC is the oral communications portion of the meeting when", "citizens may discuss their safety issues/concerns before the TSC and staff. Numerous concerns", "were discussed which sometimes lead to a change or a better understanding by all of the reason", "why something is the way it is.", "While most of the committee\u2019s time seems to surround the issues of traffic calming, bicycle and", "pedestrian safety issues and development review, these additional specific items were discussed", "and/or reviewed:", "Traffic Calming Projects/Priorities (Funding Priorities) \u2022", 